'''布隆迪'''（{{lang-de|'''Blondi'''}}，1941年 － 1945年4月29日）{{noteTag|1=亦有错误说法称其生于1934年。<ref>{{Cite book | author=Eatwell, Roger | coauthors= | title=Fascism: A History | url=https://archive.org/details/fascismhistory0000eatw | year=1995 | publisher=Chatto & Windus | location= | isbn= | page=[https://archive.org/details/fascismhistory0000eatw/page/152 152]}}</ref>}}<ref>Kershaw, Ian. ''Hitler: A Biography'', W.W. Norton & Co. p. 252. ISBN 0-393-06757-2</ref>是[[阿道夫·希特勒|阿道夫·希特勒]]饲养的一只雌性[[德國牧羊犬|德國牧羊犬]]。希特勒的个人秘书[[马丁·鲍曼|马丁·鲍曼]]於1941年把布隆迪送给希特勒。之后这只狗一直陪伴在希特勒身边。直至1945年4月，希特勒在自杀前夕，为检验毒药的效力而在布隆迪身上实验，牠也因此中毒身亡。

==经历==
布隆迪是希特勒的个人秘书[[马丁·鲍曼|马丁·鲍曼]]1941年{{noteTag|1=一说是1942年夏季。<ref>{{Cite book | author=Wires, Richard | coauthors= | title=Terminology of the Third Reich | year=1985 | publisher=Ball State University | location= | isbn= | pages=9}}</ref>}}送给他的礼物。<ref>{{Cite book | last=Comfort | first=David | coauthors= | title=The First Pet History of the World | url=https://archive.org/details/firstpethistoryo0000comf | year=1994 | publisher=Simon & Schuster | location=New York | isbn=0-671-89102-2 | page=[https://archive.org/details/firstpethistoryo0000comf/page/247 247]}}</ref>此后一直留在希特勒身边。1945年1月16日，希特勒转移至[[帝国总理府|帝国总理府]]花园地下的[[元首地堡|元首地堡]]时，也把布隆迪带在身边。<ref>{{cite book |last=Beevor |first=Antony |title=Berlin: The Downfall 1945|url=https://archive.org/details/berlindownfall190000beev_e9y1 |publisher=Viking-Penguin Books|year=2002|isbn=0-670-03041-4|page=[https://archive.org/details/berlindownfall190000beev_e9y1/page/139 139]}}</ref>1945年3月<ref>{{Cite book | author=Galante, Pierre; Silianoff, Eugène; Silianoff, Eugene | authorlink= | coauthors= | title=Voices from the Bunker | year=1989 | publisher=G.P. Putnam's | location=New York, NY | isbn=0-399-13404-2 | page=12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | author=Dekkers, Midas; Vincent, Paul | authorlink= | coauthors= | title=Dearest Pet: On Bestiality | year=2000 | publisher=Verso | location= | isbn=1-85984-310-7 | page=171}}</ref>或4月初<ref>Eberle, Henrik and Uhl, Matthias, ed. (2005). ''The Hitler Book: The Secret Dossier Prepared for Stalin'', New York: PublicAffairs, p. 188. ISBN 1-58648-366-8</ref><ref>{{Cite book | last=Brush | first=Karen A. | coauthors= | title=Everything Your Dog Expects You to Know | url=https://archive.org/details/everythingdogsex0001bush | year=2007 | publisher=New Holland Publishers Ltd | location= | isbn=1-84537-954-3 | page=[https://archive.org/details/everythingdogsex0001bush/page/108 108]}}</ref>，布隆迪与[[戈尔第·特罗斯特|戈尔第·特罗斯特]]（Gerdy Troost）的德国牧羊犬哈拉斯（Harras）生下一窝五只幼崽，其中一只被希特勒起名为“伍尔夫”（Wulf，原意为“狼”）。这是希特勒本人最喜欢的昵称，也是他自己名字“阿道夫”（Adolf，原意为“高贵的狼”）的本意。<ref>Bullock, Alan (1962). ''Adolf Hitler: A Study in Tyranny'', Penguin Books, p. 785.</ref>希特勒还开始训练伍尔夫。<ref>{{Cite book | author=Kohler, Joachim; Taylor, Ronald K. | authorlink= | coauthors= | title=Wagner's Hitler: The Prophet and His Disciple | year=2001 | publisher=Polity Press | location= | isbn=0-7456-2710-2 | page=19}}</ref>五只幼崽中的一只被留给了[[爱娃·勃劳恩|爱娃·勃劳恩]]的妹妹[[格利特·勃劳恩|格利特·勃劳恩]]（Gretl Braun），爱娃甚至给格利特寄了布隆迪和其中三只小狗的照片，并在照片中用箭头标注上送给格利特的那一只。<ref>{{Cite book | author=Gun, Nerin E. | title=Eva Braun: Hitler's Mistress | year=1969 | publisher=Meredith Press | location= | isbn=0-7456-2710-2 | pages=241, 246}}</ref>

据称希特勒本人十分喜欢布隆迪，总是把牠留在自己身边，让牠在自己地堡的卧室中睡觉。希特勒的情人爱娃·勃劳恩却并不喜欢布隆迪，她更喜欢自己的两只[[苏格兰㹴|苏格兰㹴]]（Scottish Terrier）尼格斯（Negus）和斯塔西（Stasi，又名卡图沙卡，Katuschka）。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thirdreichruins.com/berghofvisitors.htm |title=Who Was Who at Hitler's Berghof |publisher=Third Reich in Ruins |accessdate=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2015-10-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151013042800/http://www.thirdreichruins.com/berghofvisitors.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ie1FsnzQkfUC&pg=PA77&lpg=PA77&dq=negus+and+stasi&source=bl&ots=-qH1HMeKzG&sig=sKWm7yspGNDIkxfW3ijesJAgZZU&hl=en&ei=HVNWSqjIIs7KjAf3_JDXAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9 |title=Until the Final Hour: Hitler's last secretary |publisher=Arcade Publishing |year=2004 |isbn=978-1-55970-728-2 |page=77 |access-date=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2019-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004055407/https://books.google.com/books?id=ie1FsnzQkfUC&pg=PA77&lpg=PA77&dq=negus+and+stasi&source=bl&ots=-qH1HMeKzG&sig=sKWm7yspGNDIkxfW3ijesJAgZZU&hl=en&ei=HVNWSqjIIs7KjAf3_JDXAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9 |dead-url=no }}</ref>据希特勒的私人秘书[[特劳德尔·荣格|特劳德尔·荣格]]的回忆，爱娃很讨厌布隆迪，甚至曾在餐桌下用脚踢牠。<ref>Traudl Junge: Bis zur letzten Stunde. Hitlers Sekretärin erzählt ihr Leben. Claassen, Düsseldorf 2001, ISBN 3-546-00311-X (Biography of Hitler's secretary [[特劳德尔·荣格|Traudl Junge]])</ref>

1942年5月，希特勒买到另一只年轻的雌性德国牧羊犬来陪伴布隆迪，并给牠取名叫作“贝拉”（Bella）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.com.au/technology/barking-mad-hitler-trained-an-army-of-educated-talking-dogs-claims-author-dr-jan-bondeson/story-e6frfro0-1226062401875|title=Adolf Hitler had army of talking dogs, claims Dr Jan Bondeson|work=News.com.au|date=2011-05-25|access-date=2015-07-19|archive-date=2013-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622050759/http://www.news.com.au/technology/barking-mad-hitler-trained-an-army-of-educated-talking-dogs-claims-author-dr-jan-bondeson/story-e6frfro0-1226062401875|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | last=Irving | first=David John Cawdell  | coauthors= | title=Hitler's war | url=https://archive.org/details/hitlerswar0000irvi | year=1977 | publisher=Viking Press | location=New York | isbn=0-670-37412-1 | page=[https://archive.org/details/hitlerswar0000irvi/page/328 328]}}</ref>早在[[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]期间，希特勒钟爱的[[猎狐㹴|猎狐㹴]]“福克斯勒”（Fuchsl）失踪，因此非常失落。<ref name=Hubris>{{cite book | last =Kershaw | first =Ian |  year=1998 | isbn=0-393-320359 | title=Hitler 1889-1936: Hubris | url =https://archive.org/details/hitler18891936hu0000kers | publisher=Penguin Press}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | author=Giblin, James; Payne, Robert | authorlink= | coauthors= | title=The Life and Death of Adolf Hitler | url=https://archive.org/details/lifedeathofado00gibl | year=2000 | publisher=New York, Praeger [1973] | location= | isbn=0-395-90371-8 | page=[https://archive.org/details/lifedeathofado00gibl/page/20 20]}}</ref>1921年，希特勒贫困潦倒时曾得到过一只德国牧羊犬“王子”（Prinz），但不得不送到别处寄养。然而这只狗却设法逃脱，回到希特勒身边。他崇敬这只狗的忠诚和服从，从此产生了对德国牧羊犬的偏爱之心。<ref>{{cite book |last=Beevor |first=Antony |title=Berlin: The Downfall 1945|url=https://archive.org/details/berlindownfall190000beev_e9y1 |publisher=Viking-Penguin Books|year=2002|isbn=0-670-03041-4|page=[https://archive.org/details/berlindownfall190000beev_e9y1/page/357 357]}}</ref>希特勒还曾经养过一只德国牧羊犬“穆克尔”（Muckl）。<ref>{{Cite book | author=von Schirach, Baldur | coauthors= | title=Ich glaubte an Hitler | year=1967 | publisher=Mosaik Verlag | location= | isbn= | page=106}}</ref>

布隆迪在纳粹德国的政治宣传中扮演重要角色。希特勒借牠将自己塑造成热爱动物的形象，并大肆宣传自己和布隆迪之间的亲密关系。像布隆迪一样的狗也因为和狼相似，被认为是“日耳曼犬的起源”，在第三帝国流行开来。<ref>Sax, Boria (2000). ''Animals in the Third Reich: Pets, Scapegoats, and the Holocaust''. Foreword by Klaus P. Fischer. New York and London: Continuum. ISBN 978-0-8264-1289-8.</ref>

==死亡==
1945年4月29日，希特勒得知自己盟友[[贝尼托·墨索里尼|贝尼托·墨索里尼]]被意大利游击队处决，尸体被倒吊在广场上。他还得知[[苏联红军|苏联红军]]已经逐步逼近，因此下定决心终结自己的生命，以防止自己和妻子爱娃被抓，遭到和墨索里尼相同的命运。当天下午，他担心[[海因里希·希姆莱|海因里希·希姆莱]]的[[党卫队|党卫队]]给他的[[氰化物|氰化物]]胶囊是否有效。<ref>Kershaw, Ian (2008). ''Hitler: A Biography'', W.W. Norton & Co. pp. 951-953. ISBN 0-393-06757-2</ref>为了确认胶囊的毒性，希特勒命令医生[[维尔纳·哈泽|维尔纳·哈泽]]（Werner Haase）喂布隆迪服下一粒。哈泽医生把胶囊放在布隆迪口中用钳子捏碎，牠很快中毒身亡。<ref>Kershaw, Ian (2008). ''Hitler: A Biography'', W.W. Norton & Co. p. 952. ISBN 0-393-06757-2</ref>希特勒本人则为此痛苦欲绝。<ref>{{Cite book | last=O'Donnell | first=James | coauthors= | title=The Bunker: The History of the Reich Chancellery Group | year=1978 | publisher=Houghton Mifflin | location=Boston | isbn=0-395-25719-0 | page=166}}</ref>根据[[斯大林|斯大林]]授权撰写的报告以及目击证人的证词，在希特勒和爱娃自杀后的4月30日，希特勒的训狗师[[弗里茨·托诺|弗里茨·托诺]]（Fritz Tornow）把布隆迪的幼崽从戈培尔的子女手中带走，带到地堡的花园中射杀。他还杀死了爱娃的两只狗，[[戈爾達·克里斯坦|戈爾達·克里斯坦]]的狗和自己的[[腊肠犬|腊肠犬]]。之后托诺被盟军俘获。<ref>Eberle, Henrik and Uhl, Matthias, ed. (2005). ''The Hitler Book: The Secret Dossier Prepared for Stalin'', New York: PublicAffairs, p. 273. ISBN 1-58648-366-8</ref>

希特勒的护士[[埃尔娜·弗雷格|埃尔娜·弗雷格]]（Erna Flegel）在2005年时曾说，当时在元首地堡中，布隆迪的死比爱娃的死对众人的影响更大。<ref>Harding, Luke. [http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2005/may/02/artsandhumanities.secondworldwar "Hitler's nurse breaks 60 years of silence"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2005/may/02/artsandhumanities.secondworldwar |date=20121214112252 }}, ''The Guardian'', 2005-05-02.</ref>[[柏林市戰役|柏林市戰役]]结束之后，苏联反间谍特别行动机构[[施密尔舒|施密尔舒]]在一个炮弹坑中发现了希特勒和爱娃以及两只狗（据信是布隆迪和幼崽伍尔夫）的遗骸。{{noteTag|1=根据尸检，两只狗都有枪伤，布隆迪则是被毒死的，亦有资料表明伍尔夫是在之后和其他幼崽一同被杀死的。<ref>{{Cite book | last=Moorhouse | first=Roger  | coauthors= | title=Killing Hitler: The Plots, The Assassins, and the Dictator Who Cheated Death | url=https://archive.org/details/killinghitlerplo0000moor | year=2007 | publisher=Bantam | location= | isbn=0-553-38255-1 | page=[https://archive.org/details/killinghitlerplo0000moor/page/323 323]}}</ref>}}<ref>{{cite book |last=Beevor |first=Antony |title=Berlin: The Downfall 1945|url=https://archive.org/details/berlindownfall190000beev_e9y1 |publisher=Viking-Penguin Books|year=2002|isbn=0-670-03041-4|page=[https://archive.org/details/berlindownfall190000beev_e9y1/page/399 399]}}</ref>苏联方面将据信是布隆迪的遗骸挖出，并拍下了照片。<ref>le Tissier, Tony (1992). ''Berlin Then and Now'', After the Battle.</ref>

